   <mods:abstract>Ideas on ending discussions with the Spanish ambassador. Jay cannot stop
            meeting with him just because of want of powers. Jay should meet with Aranda and try to
            work out some conciliation. Of course, only the U.S. can be the judge of her pretensions
            to territory. Memoire: Spain and America are in disagreement on the limits of American
            territory. By the treaty of 1763 the Ohio territory was to remain in the hands of the
            Indians and the Mississippi to be the boundary between the territory of Britain and
            France. The Ohio territory by the proclamation of 1763 was regarded as separate from the
            13 original colonies. Spanish territory stops at 31 degrees latitude and the territory
            above this line is Indian. Line to divide Spanish and English territory west of that of
            the United States suggested. America could use the Ohio. Spain will remain in possession
            of the mouth of the Mississippi and can establish through a treaty regulation regarding
            the use of it.</mods:abstract>
